      {
        "id": "docling_jiaocaineedrop_eng-45646.pdf_30_10",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "In the cyber domain, just as in all domains, there are various factors that go into assessing risk. Risk Assessment can be viewed as a function with inputs, a process, and outputs. In general risk is viewed as a function of likelihood of occurrence of an event and impact of an event, risk( likelihood, impact ) .",
        "bbox": [
          0.08458645580357173,
          0.45930232559189627,
          0.9154135476503754,
          0.5058139529876505
        ],
        "order": 13
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_jiaocaineedrop_eng-45646.pdf_30_11",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Intuitively, if we increase the likelihood of a negative event occurring, the risk severity increases, and vice versa. This is also the case with impact, if the impact of a negative event occurring increases, the risk severity increases.",
        "bbox": [
          0.08458647441605593,
          0.5145348840773037,
          0.9154135532781789,
          0.5436507934987777
        ],
        "order": 14
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_jiaocaineedrop_eng-45646.pdf_30_13",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Likelihood of occurrence can be decomposed into two main components: threat and vulnerability. Threat is any circumstance or event that has the potential to adversely impact our system. Threat can be adversarial (purposely caused by a person) or nonadversarial (caused by an accident or natural event such as a hurricane). Vulnerability represents a weakness in an information system that can be exploited, often by an adversarial threat actor.",
        "bbox": [
          0.08458645234962463,
          0.5770348836224195,
          0.9154135476503754,
          0.6381448411822317
        ],
        "order": 16
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_jiaocaineedrop_eng-45646.pdf_30_14",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Not all vulnerabilities are equal, there are factors that we can assess a vulnerability with. The risk assessment team will ask and answer questions such as (OWASP):",
        "bbox": [
          0.08458646609710972,
          0.6468023256100649,
          0.9135338207193147,
          0.6758720930299229
        ],
        "order": 17
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_jiaocaineedrop_eng-45646.pdf_30_15",
        "observed_type": "list_item",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "(Discoverable) How easy is it for an adversary to discover the vulnerability?",
        "bbox": [
          0.08646615623220391,
          0.6845238094198451,
          0.5883458666732742,
          0.6991567459277817
        ],
        "order": 18
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_jiaocaineedrop_eng-45646.pdf_30_16",
        "observed_type": "list_item",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "(Exploitable) How easy is it for an adversary to exploit the vulnerability?",
        "bbox": [
          0.08646617258079467,
          0.7005813957405471,
          0.569548856961812,
          0.7151162788234063
        ],
        "order": 19
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_jiaocaineedrop_eng-45646.pdf_30_17",
        "observed_type": "list_item",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "(Awareness) How well known is the vulnerability?",
        "bbox": [
          0.08834587347241475,
          0.7180059522001984,
          0.42857142618923927,
          0.7296626982319443
        ],
        "order": 20
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_jiaocaineedrop_eng-45646.pdf_30_18",
        "observed_type": "list_item",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "(Detectable) How likely is an exploit to be detected?",
        "bbox": [
          0.08834588114909016,
          0.7311046512395781,
          0.4398496181616865,
          0.7456395343224373
        ],
        "order": 21
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_jiaocaineedrop_eng-45646.pdf_30_19",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Just as vulnerabilities, threats are also assessed using various factors. The risk assessment team will ask and answer questions such as (OWASP):",
        "bbox": [
          0.08270674739727568,
          0.7557043650494948,
          0.9154135367004689,
          0.7834821429149822
        ],
        "order": 22
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_jiaocaineedrop_eng-45646.pdf_30_20",
        "observed_type": "list_item",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "(Capability) How technically skilled is an adversary?",
        "bbox": [
          0.08834586886748115,
          0.7936046509552683,
          0.443609026762218,
          0.806795634735115
        ],
        "order": 23
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_jiaocaineedrop_eng-45646.pdf_30_21",
        "observed_type": "list_item",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "(Capability) How much does the adversary know about the target system?",
        "bbox": [
          0.08646616889097739,
          0.809523809726785,
          0.5733082741541353,
          0.8241567462347215
        ],
        "order": 24
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_jiaocaineedrop_eng-45646.pdf_30_22",
        "observed_type": "list_item",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "(Opportunity) Does the adversary have the resources (technology) to exploit a vulnerability?",
        "bbox": [
          0.08646617531989065,
          0.8255813949913693,
          0.6898496227735571,
          0.8415697676124513
        ],
        "order": 25
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_jiaocaineedrop_eng-45646.pdf_30_23",
        "observed_type": "list_item",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "(Opportunity) Is the adversary in a position to exploit a vulnerability?",
        "bbox": [
          0.08646618402878138,
          0.8415178572025976,
          0.5488721710840004,
          0.8561507937105342
        ],
        "order": 26
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_jiaocaineedrop_eng-45646.pdf_30_24",
        "observed_type": "list_item",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "(Intent) How motivated is an adversary to find and exploit a vulnerability?",
        "bbox": [
          0.08646616890223136,
          0.8575581399411286,
          0.5770676558722049,
          0.8720930230239877
        ],
        "order": 27
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_jiaocaineedrop_eng-45646.pdf_30_25",
        "observed_type": "list_item",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "(Intent) Does the actor performing the exploit intend harm?",
        "bbox": [
          0.08834586795112774,
          0.8735119048531376,
          0.4830827100563909,
